caption: Food was pretty good! Unfortunately, they renovated and the whole “tree in the restaurant” thing is gone, now it’s just another trendy lunch spot. Up front, every restaurant has bad days, and my experience was a bad experience. It may not be indicative of everyday experience. Don't know, only went the once and never plan on going back.  My first words upon walking out of this restaurant were "What an awful restaurant."  We waited in line for 15 minutes in front of the host desk without a single member of the staff even looking at us or explaining why we were waiting. When I finally asked a waiter what was going on, he asked the bartender, who brushed him off. No one came to speak to us.  After our wait, the host returned, I asked him why we waited for 15 minutes with no one looking at us, explaining the wait, or even standing at the host desk. He informed us that it was because they were busy. It's worth noting that not more than half the tables were occupied and roughly 15 people stood in line in front of the host.  The studious way in which the staff ignored us is truly remarkable. Half a dining room full of people standing in front of the host desk with nary a glance or rough approximation of acknowledgment in our direction.  The food itself was average and barely worth the price paid. Let me be clear, the food was NOT bad, I just don't think it was great. My home fries were cold in the middle, the eggs Benedict was acceptable.  I spoke with the manager who offered a free mimosa, something I'm not interested in.  At the end of the meal, I paid $55 plus a tip for some granola and vanilla yogurt, 2 poached eggs with hollandaise sauce, and an English muffin with a side of lettuce.  Bad days happen, I get that, but bad service with mediocre food is not something to brag about.

Had lunch here and would definitely recommend it to others. The drinks were great and the food was good too. I cannot rage about the drinks enough. The server was nice and attentive to our group's needs.

Just wanted to say that my friends and I had a great time yesterday during brunch. Our reservation was made for 4 and some of my friends decided to join and it changed to 6, the hostess was very accommodating and so nice about it. One of my friends did mention she had an allergy to nuts and ordered the granola parfait and asked for no nuts, the server asked if it was an allergy or just a preference which was very considerate and also mentioned that cross contamination might be a factor. My friend did let him know that she was ok with that. We appreciated the service from hostess to the waiter. Definitely coming back in the future.  Also as irritating as separate checks   can be, our server did not make it seem like it was an issue.

We were seated early & given a delicious cocktail, included with dinner. The amuse & app came out promptly but we had to wait a while for our entrees. Heard about Firefly through Travelzoo and I had a discount voucher. I liked the decor when we came in - the tree theme speaks to my love of the outdoors. We started with a beer and a cocktail. Good list of cocktail options, limited beer list but good quality local beers across a variety of styles. We picked the scallops appetizer since we intended to share. Didn't realize the scallops were raw! I enjoy that but my wife doesn't. But she ate the golden beets. A little heavy on the poppy seeds, but enjoyable. I had the pot roast and my wife had the duck. Both were very good - we finished to the last bite! The pot roast was fork tender. Nothing unusual, just good comfort food. We ended with the chocolate creme du pot. Tasted just like chocolate pudding but the whipped cream and cocoa nibs were a good addition. The service was excellent throughout the meal, not overbearing, always cheerful. A bit pricey, not sure I would have gone without the voucher.

The pace is next to our office so we used to go go here quite often. They have a new chef and it's utter disaster. If you are planning a lunch because you liked their signature entrees a year ago, don't bother. The new chef has even replaced the menu. We asked for few of our favorite dishes and were told the new chef does not make them anymore. Not sure for how long they can survive.
My go to for brunch whenever anyone is in from ot if town!  Everything is so delicious!
Great service, awesome atmosphere, and really good food... Intimate and quiet
Brunch is cramped and crowded and service is disorganized and slow. Food is meh and options are pretty basic. There are much better places for brunch in the area that are worth the price.

Best brussel sprouts I've ever had, mix it with the scallops instead of the squash that the entree comes with and it will melt in your mouth. Seasoned steak was also very flavorful-not Ruth's Chris but still good.
The servings are very large.  I had the French toast at lunch time and hadn't eaten breakfast.  I was not able to finish it, which is unusual for me.
Firefly is slightly overpriced for what it is, but the french toast is good.
Horrible bloody Mary.
Great gluten free menu at reasonable prices. Love their deviled eggs!
Sit at the bar, Mike will definitely take care of you!!
Sat at the bar for 15 minutes, got no service so we walked out. If your looking for a free meal sit at the bar and just wait for the opportunity to walk out.

Good biscuits and gravy. $6 orange juice is a little beyond me, I don’t care if it’s fresh squeezed or whatever. Server was slow to get to us when we got there and initially brought a water pitcher that was 1/3 full; only filled my glass 3/4’s of the way and my boyfriends was left empty. Food was really good. But I put a lot of emphasis on customer service and overall experience of a meal- even if it’s brunch.
The Mac and cheese on the kids menu is life changing!
I enjoyed lunch good service great food .

Ordered a Vine and Fig Tree which is made with a smoked bourbon. I was a little apprehensive to drink it after having a "smoked" drink at another local and rather forgettable bar, but Brendan assured me that it was well balanced and not over powering. I trusted his expertise and was pleasantly surprised by the craft and skill that was used to make the drink. A new favorite place to frequent for great craft cocktails and atmosphere.
Food, was ok. Service was slow. The pig wings appetizer... we're small pork ribs with little/no meat one them. I had the grass feed beef burger ordered medium but it came out rare.!

I have only ever had breakfast here, but it is consistently good. They put an emphasis on fresh ingredients and a changing menu. The staff works their butts off and are always so sweet. Service can be a little slow but That’s the kitchen. The decor is cool. I really like the rustic feel with a modern twist. I will someday try a meal other than breakfast, but I usually get in late and have eaten on the way. If you’re going for breakfast I highly recommend the french toast. It is my favorite but I can’t eat it every time because it is decadent. The eggs are great too. It’s usually not too crowded in the mornings. I think you’ll like it.

I don’t know about this complimentary pound cake I read about but the food was fantastic. The pot roast was pretty amazing. Opted for the pork belly and, while it was really good, the pot roast has been a signature dish for years. Shouldn’t ever doubt something like that.
Carafe of mimosas is a good deal. Great prosciutto eggs Benedict.
I hate it. I was terrible.
(Translated by Google) Excellent place they have waiters who speak Spanish and the food very good  (Original) Excelente lugar tienen mozos que hablan castellano y la comida muy buena

Went for their brunch. Though the prices of the mimosas were good ($3) I was a bit shocked by the price of the main course (high teens). I ordered Eggs Benedict. The yolks were hard which I consider a sin for Eggs Benedict. They were also very cold as if they had been waiting out for a bit. The hollandaise had almost solidified on top. I was not the exception either. Another member of my table ordered the same dish and had the same problems. For $17 I expected better. Coffee was $5 for mediocre drip coffee, not an espresso drink. We had also called a few days prior to change the size of our reservation to smaller but when we got there the changes had not been logged and they sat us down at a table for 4 more seats than we needed. This isn't a bad thing for us, but it definitely reflects miscommunication in the restaurant. The atmosphere and decor of Firefly is cute and trendy and that definitely helped a lot. Overall I was very disappointed as I have heard so many good things about Firefly before and felt underwhelmed by the food.
This place was a pleasure. The bartender showed a lot of passion in what he does. I enjoyed my food and drinks.

With a lunch reservation, our large group (>8) were seated quickly. The food was okay, with notable exceptions from the group being the pleasant (and overpriced) truffle fries, the flavorful spicy shrimp grits and the uninspired regretful omelette and greens.  There were few vegetarian options on the menu (Feb 2018, different from what is posted on their site) and none were particularly exciting. While they mentioned more options to come in their next menu, none of the party were very inclined to return.  Besides this, our stay was enjoyable as it was not crowded and service was polite and friendly.  Note for other large parties: they do not split the check, expect 20% gratuity and it may take a while before your food comes, which is all understandable. Finally, it is not a real tree that is featured indoors. More like a "Keebler" elves kind of tree.  Hope that helps!
Food was delicious but had to wait a long time to get it
Killer drinks Brendan! Be back soon!
Excellent brunch

The atmosphere was amazing. Very relaxing. Our waiter Rio was very nice. He recommended the pork chop which was very delicious. I love the way everyone makes sure you're satisfied. I look fordward to coming again.

Terrible.  We ordered the truffle fries to start. The bottom of the basket was ice cold but they topped the basket off with warm fries.  Gross. It was weird.  Then my Husband ordered the cioppino (mussels).  He took one bite and sand!! He sent it back (as did I as this was a Valentine’s Day dinner).  When our food came out again, my trout (which was fine before I sent it back) was served skin up.  The first time they served it to me skin down.  I thought it was weird.  One bite and I knew why!!! They over peppered it.  Like big time.  To the point where I couldn’t eat it.  We decided to leave.  The manager gave us his card and offered us a free meal if we go back.  We may or may not.  Our waiter was nice, though.

Great food, but the service was lacking. Came here for brunch with some friends. The restaurant was bustling but not overcrowded. Complementary pound cake and rolls were quickly delivered to our table. Solid brunch menu with vegetarian options. Server seemed friendly, but had to be asked to refill our water and sometimes we he would only fill half of the waters and would not come back to fill the rest. Took a while to deliver our drinks and complained that he didn’t have time to divide up the check between 3 cards. There were plenty of empty tables  :/ While our meal was tasty, we will likely not come back due to the service.
Always delicious! Meatloaf was incredible. And they have a separate gluten free menu, yay!
Fries were delicious. Happy Hour prices are a good value for some good drinks. Make sure to ask about it though! We had to ask to get the HH menu. The decor was beautiful.
This place is very nice! Complimentary bread is delicious! I had the mini pot roast it was good especially the potatoes. Music playlist #fuego

Me and my friends/ family had an amazing time. I made reservations and they were very understanding when I called to say I would be late. Our waitress paid for my birthday dessert. The atmosphere was very warm and inviting, definitely kid friendly, the view is great, there's a tree in the middle of the room which enticed my decision to actually eat here. The drinks were very interesting. Bathroom was fairly clean, handicap accessible, not too high priced! I loved it, definitely see myself going back.

Outstanding food and service. I often travel to DC for business and chose the Madera hotel this time. I love my room and am delighted that the quality of the food matched the easy accessibility of the restaurant after my long flight. I had the acorn squash salad, shrimp and grits, and a glass of pinot gris. Not as swanky as some of the Kimpton properties, more down to earth, in a good way. All of the employees were attentive and charming and I plan to visit again.
The

Me likey.  Food was fantastic.  Easily accommodated weird food restrictions.  Weren't perturbed by children, had kid menu and bake-your-own cookie activity.  Waiter Rachel was extremely helpful and my beer never ran dry.  Definitely going back.
Great staff, great food, great dessert, great ambiance.  Wish I lived closer!
Was there with family for Christmas Eve brunch.  My polenta with spinach, mushrooms, and poached eggs was savory and filling.  We all enjoyed our meals. Service was quick and friendly.
Can't miss Brendan tending bar. He's a master cocktail craftsman.

In fifrefly I had three of the absolutely worst dishes of my life! There is NO EXCUSE for dishes like: 1. The wedge salad. Literally a wedge of iceberg, a few cherry tomatoes on the side, cardboard hard bacon bits, and a dressing. This I would not serve even to my dog, who lies green stuff. 2. The charcuterie board. A shame for the restaurant! For USD 17 you get something like 6 paper thin slices of below medium quality cured meats that bear no identity, 3. The cheese board. Another shameful dish. For USD 16 you get three (!) SMALL pieces of cheese, one of which is a cheddar, the other is a disnitegrating chevre, and the third looked like brie, but I did not bother to taste. The restaurant manager must take all these three dishes out of the menu immediately.
Great home cooking. Pot roast is legendary
Good place to eat
The truffle fries are amazing!! I wanted to order two of them. And the bartender Brendan is amazing! His drinks are superb. Definitely will come back.
Love the atmosphere. Relaxing and hip. The drinks are great. The food is amazing. And the staff is topl notch!
Exceeds expectations!
Good service.   Reasonable  prices.

Went with a medium group (about 16) for lunch, our orders were taken reasonably quickly, but it took about an hour for the food to come out. 2 of us ordered our burgers medium and they came out very well done and dry. My bacon was no where to be seen. The back room has terrible acoustics and it was hard to hold a conversation with anyone without shouting. The only reason this isn't a 1 star review is because the staff was nice and the truffle fries are delicious.

I went with a group of people and one of us was celiac. The restaurant has a separate gluten free menu and they were very celiac friendly. One of the dishes came out with bread on top when it should have been on the side (it was supposed to be shared) and the wait staff was so sweet and apologetic. They gave us a free gluten free dessert to make up for it!
HORRIBLE HORRIBLE HORRIBLE SERVICE!!!! Even with a reservation we waited over 20 minutes. No apology, nothing!
Great brunch and service!
Delicious pumpkin soup. 'Lounge' is not very lounge- like but otherwise a nice cozy setting. Server was not very familiar with the food but good service otherwise.
(Translated by Google) Delicious and very friendly and good ~  (Original) 맛있고 매우 친절하게 대하고 좋아요~

Firefly has a few strikes against them and it's warranted. First off, it's a restaurant in a hotel. Secondly, it's only three stars on Yelp. Finally, their main selling point is a giant tree in the middle of the restaurant. Enough said.  I met the CEO of the Muse here for a small group discussion about the future of work. We had a small back room reserved that was very quiet. The service was fast and hands on, but the food was just okay. I ordered the pumpkin soup (which was the stand out dish of the lunch) and a reuben that was mediocre.  If you're a hotel guest, there's worst places to dine, but in a city full of top restaurants, I'd spend time researching other options.

A small and interestingly-decorated concept restaurant attached to a boutique hotel within convenient walking distance from the DuPont Circle Metro stop. The food is slightly on the pricier side, but absolutely delicious and the service was very friendly. The menu is comprised of inventive and seasonal dishes - definitely try the pumpkin cheesecake french toast! There's a taste for every palate and the atmosphere of the restaurant is fun and unique. Definitely would recommend!
Great food and great service! Went for brunch, would recommend to anyone visiting!
Overpriced for the quality.
A decade ago it was a great date spot. It still is! Good drinks, great ambiance, worth more than once a decade entrance
Excellent food (lamb chops amazing), but it took some prodding to get our food out after quite a long time. Family friendly

i am from the UK and went here with 2 friends from the USA.  I could not fault it.  great service to begin with and attentive throughout within being bothersome.  we were there during restaurant month. so they had a great deal on a 3 course set menu.  steak was perfect to my orders an i simply could not fault any of the food my party ate.  the beer and wine selection complimented the meal perfectly and there was a fantastic selection of craft ales.. if you are stuck with somewhere to go in DC i recommend this place Casual dining at its best.
One of the best places I have eaten in the district. l.p.

Very disappointed, ordered a gluten free burger with fries from the gluten free menu. Came with no bread and the fries weren't provided as they are cooked in a fryer where other gluten products are cooked. As a type one diabetic with coeliac disease this was a bad restaurant to choose, gluten free menu was limited.
Took forever to get food. Need better options for kids.

I had different expectations of this place and was a bit disappointed. The restaurant inside is tiny  and with more people in the evening I imagine you'd have to shout to have a conversation. Food not too good either, especially the shrimp and grits - the shrimps tasted exactly like supermarket defrosted ones !

One rude unfriendly server with lack of menu knowledge. Gluten free options are just normal meals with gluten aspects removed not substituted - you will not be informed beforehand. You get the feeling that gluten free diners should just be grateful they're even willing to cater for us.  Side portions are pathetically small for a $7 charge. The food i did managed to eat however was tasty and cooked well! Overall a poor dining experience mostly ruined by a cold, butch, racially prejudiced female server.
Quality service, great menu and amazing unique drink selection

The staff was friendly and the server was really attentive (but not overbearing). Food was also good! It's not as expensive to grab a bite as other DC places. Low key but really nice! I have gone several times and no complaints!
Good but on the pricy side
The pot roast was like butter! Flavorful and just a pleasure to eat with perfectly cooked carrots and potatoes. Thank goodness I couldn't finish it. Leftovers for tomorrow!!
Poor service, slow kitchen, food was mediocre at best. Maybe I caught it on a bad night, but I would never go back.
Great food, great service.  We were very impressed!
Great location with a chill setting!
Great food. It's delicious and refreshing. A must for breakfast if you're in the area. Also very vegan/vegetarian-friendly.
Food and ambiance
Decent breakfast. Scrambled eggs were a bit overdone and the toast was dry. But the sausages were good, as was the French toast.

Worst Mother's Day brunch! The restaurant was very dated and run down (dusty decor, stained seat cushions, etc.). We had a reservation and there were so many open tables in the main dining room, but we were pushed back into a dingy, windowless back room. They refused to reseat us. Service was slow and inattentive. 3 requests for a refill on coffee resulted in...no more coffee for us. Ugh!
Not a bad atmosphere but the lamb was fatty and lacked flavor. The portions and quality weren't great for the price.
Will the bartender is fantastic!  He is extremely personable and adds character to sitting at the bar.  I would recommend going to Firefly for happy hour!  Good drink prices and great service!
Nice cocktails, but the food is just ok

Took my girlfriend here because I read that it had a very gluten-free friendly menu. First off, the wait we encountered for our reserved table was not a great way to start off our experience. The menu was all right but definitely not as many gluten-free options or any willingness to accommodate that diet as I was expecting. Our small plates were good, I personally wish I had just ordered two of the fried oyster plates instead of one and getting the crab cakes. I was really disappointed with my crab cakes and I can say it wasn't cheap being that disappointed. My girlfriend liked her pot roast. Honestly, you can probably find the same food here done better somewhere else for less.
Go-to place to take friends and family when they come to town to visit. Brunch is the best of the meal options.
Loved this place when my boyfriend and I visited D.C. we were both very happy with our meals and the service. They have great food!

We came here for a quick brunch. Firefly has a great atmosphere and the waiter was really friendly. The corned beef hash I had was pretty good, made with real corned beef and bell peppers and onions instead of the traditional potatos. My …
Went with a larger group. They were very accommodating. The gentleman at the front desk seemed overly stressed and not enjoying his job.  My meal was OK...Good but not great.
Small hotel restaurant serving inventive dishes (was there for brunch).  Friendly helpful staff.  Interesting decor concept, built around a tree.

Excellent food. My husband and I were greeted and waited on by Stephanie. She was extremely sweet and helpful. We are tourists to the dc area and are not used to the busy hustle and bustle. She made us feel at home with some very nice small talk and got our hot tea, coffee, and food order in very quickly. I had the steel oats with cranberry compote which was delicious! The atmosphere is very inviting. I'd love to stay here in one of the rooms just to eat at Firefly everyday of my stay! Absolutely recommending this place to everyone that I know coming to the area :)

Stopped by for Sunday brunch with my girlfriend on a sightseeing weekend trip to D.C. The French toast was delicious and the service was excellent. Wasn't thrilled with the location of the table we were seated at, sandwiched in between two loud parties. Other than that, it was great. We'll be back the next time we're in town
The mini pot roast is to die for. It's an indoor picnic with comfort food.

Firefly was one of the first places I went out for dinner and drinks after I moved to D.C. My bartender was incredibly nice and after finding out I was new to town went to the effort of writing me a list of places to check out - bars, restaurants, museums, and neighbourhoods. Thank you so much!

The food is good, but what really sells the place is the bartender. He is amazing with drinks and makes the most amazing things. He had one that was lemon sorbet, grapefruit something, and wine I think (I don't know exactly but it was amazing). He's there Friday.
Nice place, food is not amazing.
Food & service hit the mark it's a place to re-visit for me!

A group of 6 stopped in here on a Saturday night without reservations. There was no wait so they got a table together in short order to seat us. The drinks were good, service was great. Menu is not huge but from the burger to the pot roast, it was all delicious.
Good

A decent but slightly expensive place for drinks. Martinis and Manhattans are nice and strong. The bar and dining area features an artificial tree that, combined with other features in the restaurant, make for an interesting ambiance. The fried oysters were particularly delicious.
